a_2=\frac{1}{2}-\frac{1}{3}
a_{100}=\frac{1}{100}-\frac{1}{101}
1-\frac{1}{101} = \frac{100}{101}
a_1+a_2+a_3+\cdots+a_{99}+a_{100}
=\left(1-\frac{1}{2}\right)+ \left(\frac{1}{2}-\frac{1}{3}\right)+\left(\frac{1}{3} - \frac{1}{4} \right) \cdots+\left(\frac{1}{99} - \frac{1}{100}\right) + \left( \frac{1}{100} - \frac{1}{101} \right).
1 + \left(-\frac{1}{2} + \frac{1}{2}\right) + \left(-\frac{1}{3} + \frac{1}{3}\right) + \cdots +\left(-\frac{1}{100} + \frac{1}{100} \right) - \frac{1}{101}
=1-\frac{1}{101} = \frac{100}{101}.
